## Wazuh Installation — Ubuntu VM

### Download Installation Script
```bash
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.11/wazuh-install.sh
```

What curl does:
- curl = Client URL
- Downloads content from internet directly into terminal
- `-s` = Silent mode — don't show download progress
- `-O` = Save file with its original filename

### Verify Download
```bash
ls -lh wazuh-install.sh
```

### Run Installation (All In One)
```bash
sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a
```
`-a` = Install everything together (Server + Indexer + Dashboard)

Takes 15-30 minutes. Do NOT close terminal during installation.

### Get Login Credentials
```bash
sudo tar -O -xvf wazuh-install-files.tar wazuh-install-files/wazuh-passwords.txt
```
Look for:
```
indexer_username: 'admin'
indexer_password: 'your-generated-password'
```

### Open Required Firewall Ports
```bash
sudo ufw allow 443    # Wazuh dashboard
sudo ufw allow 1514   # Agent communication
sudo ufw allow 1515   # Agent enrollment
sudo ufw reload
```

### Access Dashboard
```
https://YOUR-VM-IP
Username: admin
Password: (from wazuh-passwords.txt)
```

