## Wazuh Agent Installation — Windows

### Open PowerShell As Administrator
1. Press Windows Key
2. Type PowerShell
3. Right click → Run as Administrator
4. Click Yes

Why Administrator? Same as sudo in Linux — needed for installing software and managing services.

### Download Agent
```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/windows/wazuh-agent-4.11.2-1.msi -OutFile $env:USERPROFILE\Desktop\wazuh-agent.msi
```

Invoke-WebRequest = PowerShell equivalent of curl — downloads files from internet.

### Install Agent
```powershell
msiexec.exe /i $env:USERPROFILE\Desktop\wazuh-agent.msi /q WAZUH_MANAGER='YOUR-VM-IP' WAZUH_AGENT_NAME='your-agent-name'
```

| Part | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `msiexec.exe` | Windows MSI installer |
| `/i` | Install |
| `/q` | Silent — no popup windows |
| `WAZUH_MANAGER` | IP of Wazuh Server |
| `WAZUH_AGENT_NAME` | Name for this device |

### Start Agent Service
```powershell
NET START WazuhSvc
```

### Stop Agent Service
```powershell
NET STOP WazuhSvc
```

### Check Agent Status
```powershell
Get-Service | findstr -i wazuh
```

---

## Verify Agent Connection — Ubuntu VM
```bash
sudo /var/ossec/bin/agent_control -l
```

| Result | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Active | Agent connected and sending logs ✅ |
| Disconnected | Agent installed but not communicating ⚠️ |
| Never connected | Agent never reached server ❌ |

